questions.scenario:
You are debugging a production issue where a Spring Boot application running on an embedded Tomcat server experiences a slow memory leak, eventually leading to `OutOfMemoryError: Java heap space`. Analyzing the heap dump reveals millions of `TenantContext` and `String` instances retained by `WebContainer` thread locals. Below is the interceptor responsible for context propagation:

java
@Component
public class TenantInterceptor implements HandlerInterceptor {
    @Override
    public boolean preHandle(HttpServletRequest request, HttpServletResponse res, Object handler) {
        String tenantId = request.getHeader("X-Tenant-ID");
        TenantContextHolder.set(new TenantContext(tenantId));
        return true;
    }
}
